body:
> As an African, living in Africa.. your “tell it to the starving children” is so condescending.

How is it condescending? There is no shortage of struggling children, they are all over the planet. I could have just as well used America or Asia, I just think it's probably worse over in Africa.

>Stay in your little privileged bubble where mental health struggles (despite living in a country with facilities to help you available) is the biggest problem in your life.

Now who is being condescending. Mental illness is no joke. If your brain doesn't work properly, living a normal life is not possible.

>You go to bed at night with a roof over your head, a full belly (because you’re blessed enough to live in a country without famine or the negative impacts of war) and in your free time you’re fantasizing about the end of the world and how devastating disasters all over the world are happening to further YOUR curiosity.

What does this have to do with whether Christianity is real or not?

>I’m sorry about your reality but you don’t have it that bad.

You haven't lived in my shoes, so you don't know anything. But this has nothing to do with Christianity.

>You must be American… you think God revolves around you and the things he hasn’t given you, despite discounting all the daily things you take for granted.

I'm not American and as an agnostic I don't know if god is real or not. Life is unfair, innocent people suffer for no good reason while evil people live full and happy lives in comfort. But if I have to thank anyone I will thank my family, ancestors and countrymen for the good things I have in my life. They have helped me when the Christian god did not, because he isn't real.

title: WTW for something that could be taken two ways without context?
body:
An example would be "bite me." I could either be telling you to go away or literally telling you to bite me. It's where without context, it could be taken either way.

Edit: I'm Norwegian, English is a hard language.

Ignorance is bliss I guess

body:
I live on what's essentalially a temporary sickness pension (I'm Finnish) - I have to renew it every year or so to keep it running, otherwise it's just like I'd have retired. My doctor and I have been trying to get a more lasting retirement/pension for me for a few years now, and it's only a matter of time before they allow it for me.

I'm 26, never worked, and I think I never will. But I'm okay with that. This way I can live relatively stress free, making my condition as stable as it can be, and I can try and concentrate on living as happy as possible - seeing friends, playing video games and composing/listening to music pretty much is everything I've got going on at the moment. And I'm relatively happy with how things are.

body:
Depends on very much where you live. I'm Finnish. I presume you are from USA, and I have a reason to believe that things are very different here, but I'm no expert. I do personally know a few who have suffered a sentence in here, so I know more about finnish prisons than I do about those from the states. 

Not that I'd be ok going to prison either way, mostly 'cause I'd have to fear rape in a mens prison while just getting beaten up in womens (in finland, people can decide which prison sector to go to according to their gender identity), and I ain't no fighter.

title: What's life like in Armenia?
body:
I'm thinking of traveling to Armenia once I get my degree in the states and living there for a while, I'm a 27 year old female. I'm Armenian, but born in California. 

I can work from home in Armenia as a graphic designer for a company that I currently work for and make money that way. How much does rent cost in US dollars for a studio apt or 1 bedroom? Are there busses that go to most places? I don't drive. What kind of shops are around? Do most people speak English also? 

Thanks!

title: Do you think this drink would be OK in my pre-op liquid diet?
body:
I'm Armenian and we have this drink called, "Tahn", it's basically unflavored plain **yogurt** mixed with **water** and **salt** until it's all liquid. I like to blend it with lots of ice and make it kind of a smoothie. 

Think it'll be ok? I'll ask my doctors office next week but I just thought I'd get some feedback from you guys first. I don't know if my doctor's office is open Monday because of Memorial Day.

title: Hate against Mulan
body:
I’m feeling kind of shitty.  My friends (white) are posting about Mulan and how it’s a shitty movie and we should boycott it because of the treatment of the Uyghurs in China. It makes me feel kind of bad because Asians can’t get anything. Everything for us is “bad” in some way. It’s so frustrating. Like..  I was kind of happy to see so many Asian faces and actors in Mulan, even though I didn’t like the writing. Honestly the only reason I think some people are upset about the Uyghurs is because it’s trendy and because they look like white people. And it’s another reason to hate China.

It feels kind of bad when your home country is constantly shit on all the damn time.  A lot of my friends or adults are proud of their heritage or home country.  I can’t be proud of mine though because I’ll be called a “communist spy”, “CCP supporter” or “brainwashed.”

I’m not saying Mulan was a great movie, it’s not. I didn’t like it and I think it had a lot of issues, like stereotyping and being written by all white people.  I guess I’m just so starved of Asian representation and seeing all those Asian actors seemed so amazing to me. Like, I’d never seen that before.  I don’t know...

Sorry for the dump. I’m just feeling kind of down. I hate being Asian because most people just don’t get it.  I want to scream into the void because I feel so misunderstood.  The Uyghur situation is bad and I hate what’s happening to them in China, but it seems like anything that has to do with China gets criticized because of the Uyghurs.  It’s always connected to something being Chinese. The main point of the post was about the Uyghurs, several pages later talked about colorism, stereotypes, and being whitewashed. It was like those things were just added as afterthoughts. 

The account that everyone was sharing is called @freeuyghurnow in case anyone wants to look up the original post.

body:
I feel like I was brainwashed into believing I am white.

Despite the reality that I am Chinese, I don't get the validation from other Chinese people that I am one of them, and I don't get the validation from other white people that I am one of them either. I've been ostracized by my own racial group and have been blamed for being 'too white' while not being white enough to reap ANY of the benefits. I feel like I can't claim to be a person of color because I have to acknowledge and be thankful for my 'white privilege' that my white adopted parents 'gifted' me. Never mind the fact that I can't have white privilege because I'm NOT white. Yet I've been treated again and again like it's my fault or choice that I have white parents. I can't think of any other word to describe these feelings I've been forced to confront besides brainwashing. And I'm still not completely recovered. 

It's utter insanity and all the question of validity does is gaslight, abuse, and invalidate transracial adoptees. Society needs to stop treating adoptees like this. It's cruel.

body:
It infuriates the fuck out of me that the term “transracial” has been tainted and co-opted by these bozos who want to be a different race. 

Transracial is a term originally used for adopted people who were adopted into a family of a different race than them (example: black baby adopted into a white family). It doesn’t mean changing your race, it means dealing with lifelong identity problems and trauma due to being integrated into a completely different culture than from your birth. I’m a transracial adoptee. I am Chinese but my adoptive parents are white. I will continue to fight for our term, and try and educate others on its real meaning.

I’m not accusing you or anything, I just want people to know what transracial is supposed to mean originally.

title: WIBTBF if I dropped my close friends?
body:
I (14M) have 3 close friends , 1 is my cousin , we'll call him gary(14M) , 2nd is my brother , we'll call him bob(15M) , and the 3rd one is my best friend who we'll call Matt(15M) . All of us are Cree/First nations

Recently garys been very racist , sexist , overall an asshole, he picks on Matt alot , because he's lighter skin tone than us, which is dumb but whatever, and well, Matt doesn't do shit about it . He always talks about how much he doesn't like Gary , then he goes all buddy buddy besties with him a minute later ? l honestly don't understand it. Just last week we were talking about possibly contacting the office about Gary's behavior, but he didn't want to get his parents involved so that went nowhere. gary will say the most racist shit and then when you try calling him out on it , he either says 'its just a joke" or "it's because I'm brown ". He makes jokes about being mexican, says stereotypical shit , when I say anything he literally just says "cus I'm brown" .. no it's because your a racist peice of shit. anyways moving on from him , Matt has been doing the same shit as Gary , basically copying him , I've been diagnosed with schizophrenia, he always makes stupid triggering jokes like "I'm not real" "you forgot your meds" "this isn't real" which fucking sucks because he's literally the person I'm the closest to in this "friend group" and he jokes about my serious mental illnesses like they're fucking nothing. so obviously I want to drop the both of them , right? But here where bob comes in, bob is good friends with landon, still kind of friends with will , so if I dropped them, and kept hanging out with bob, they'd try to talk to me because me and bob sit near them, I know this because I tried to cut off Gary but he kept thinking he could talk to me because I was sitting with matt, Matt was sitting kinda close to Gary, so he took that as an OK to talk to me ,which it wasn't, I went to the counselor and she basically said I had 3 options : go to the principal, try to talk to them about their behaviour, or suck it up and move on. 
which is ass, but I think moving on will be the best option, so that's what I want to do but i don't wanna have to cut / limit contact with my brother cause of those asshats.

So uh, WIBTA if I dropped me and my brother's close friends?

TLDR; I wanna cut off 2 assholes but my brother is friends with them and I don't wanna cut my brother off by cutting them off

hopefully I did this right this time

title: SOT needs regional matchmaking
body:
I've just tried joining about 20 different open galleons and every single one of them spoke chinese. It's super annoying and dissapointing when I want to be able to communicate with my crew yet the only word I know is ni hao. Not only that but when I solo/duo sloop with my friend we can't even talk to anyone in the server because they also all speak chinese.  


I live in Australia so even if they don't have servers here they should give us the option to connect to servers in other english speaking countries rather than just the server with the lowest ping. I would happily give up that tiny bit of extra ping. There has been a few times I've managed to connect to english servers and the experience of this game has been infinitely more satisfying and memorable.   


I only have 80 hours and play on pc so if there's any way to change servers feel free to enlighten me. There is always discord but I shouldn't have to use another app just to match with people who actually speak english. Does anyone else experience this same problem?

title: [Wanted][Semi-vanilla]{18+}{European}
body:
I'm looking for an 18+ server based in Europe. The reason for that is that I want to have other players be active during the same time as me. I speak Danish, Norwegian and English (and I can make myself understood in Swedish), so it would be cool if there were other Scandinavians / Nothern Europeans as well.

I'd prefer it to be semi vanilla, but I don't mind non-altering plugins like McMMo.

I'd also like the map to be fairly new, I don't want to have to travel 3000k blocks before finding a viable base site.

I'd like it to be a server with an active Discord server, preferably one where jokes and swearwords are tolerated (in moderation, of course)

And I'd prefer if it was whitelisted. I feel whitelisting provides a better sense of quality as well as keeps out the griefers and the assholes.

Other than that, I don't have any preferences, but it would be nice if the server wasn't set to 'hard'.

I hope there's someone out there with a server that fits my needs.

title: [TOMT] [ANIMATED KID SHOW] [2000's/2010's] very simple for young kids with a blond doll-like girl with blue boutons eyes
body:
It's been a while now since I started searching this kid show.
First, it was on a DVD format. Characters were not able to talk, but there was a narrator explaining what's happening on screen. 

The entire show was taking place in a world very simple, each characters has it own house. The ground was green and the sky was blue. There were multiple characters but I can only remember of one clearly.
It's a blonde girl with 2 draids, looking like a doll with blue boutons eyes and dressed in pink. Her house was pink as well. 
Episodes were short, no link between them and very very simple.
In one episode I remember characters were trying to make stilts with paint bucket. 
I think the girl was cooking too and there was a marine...but not very sure.

If you can help me with that I'll be so happy, thanks for reading if you have any questions I'll answer to it if can in the comments.

(+ i'm French if that can help and it was in French)

title: Hello!
body:
Hello everyone,

I am schisisite and I have schizophrenia for almost 25 years...I have been writing about it for years. [Everyday life with schizophrenia](https://schisissite.wordpress.com/) is blog in english. As I am from Croatia I have got a blog in Croatian Šiza je samo kriza [https://blog.dnevnik.hr/nalicje/?page=blog&subdomain=nalicje](https://blog.dnevnik.hr/nalicje/?page=blog&subdomain=nalicje). 

My personal belief and experience is that in spite of schizophrenia one can contribute and be as valuable member of society as any other "normal" person. ... It is more difficult for schizophrenic people because our issues are often severe and our crisis can be deep. Schizophrenia has so many different faces but even there are very tough days there are others that makes life worth living...Today has been a long day for me because I got up at 4,30 AM local time, and now 16 hours later I am ready for my meds and sleep.

Type soon.

body:
I'm new here and I just wanted to say hello. I was 20xx at the time I don't remember I'm drunk and high right now. (I live in Germany). And I just don't know what to do with my feelings anymore. My opinions on certain things change and vary every day. I don't know what to do with myself because I have to retrain myself every day to master my own self. I was diagnosed with paranoid schizophrenia and for years I convinced myself that I was healthy, but now I realize that it's all a lie and I really am ill. This may all sound cringeworthy, I'm just writing down my thoughts here. And now I have no idea what I wanted to write, so I'll stop now.

I have been diagnosed with paranoid schizophrenia and am manic-depressive with symptoms of severe borderline disorder. I just don't know what to do anymore so I'm turning to this sub.

I wrote this with deepl.com so forgive me for mistakes but I can't think straight right now

title: An introduction to Dü’osr̈aï - a very simple artlang designed to teach myself more about linguistics. Just a beginner, please be kind, very nervous sharing.
body:
**Phonology**

The inspiration for making the sounds of this conlang began from a habit where I would sometimes try to pronounce an acronym as quickly as I could and imagine the names of the letters made a word of its own. (For example, say "PNG" as fast as you can)

When setting out to make the conlang, this progressed to the idea that every letter has two official sounds, the first derived from English (understanding that's not the best), the second one being the 'name' of the letter as said in English, marked with an umlaut simply because I like the aesthetics, and stresses are usually on these letters. Because of this, there is no "w" or "ẅ" as literally saying "double ü" seems silly, so I've limited it to 25 letters, but it ends up being 50 altogether.

Here's my best attempt at some phonetic tables.

Vowels

|**Grapheme**|**Phoneme**|**Grapheme**|**Phoneme**|
|:-|:-|:-|:-|
|a|æ|ä|eɪ|
|**e**|e|**ë**|i|
|**i**|ɪ|**ï**|aɪ|
|**o**|ɒ|**ö**|oʊ|
|**u**|u|**ü**|ju|

Consonants

|b|b|b̈|bi|
|:-|:-|:-|:-|
|**c**|tʃ|**c̈**|si|
|**d**|d|!|di|
|**f**|f|!|ef|
|**g**|**g** |!|dʒi|
|**h**|h|**ḧ**|eɪtʃ|
|**j**|dʒ|**j̈**|dʒeɪ|
|**k**|k|**k̈**|keɪ|
|**l**|l|**l̈**|el|
|**m**|m|**m̈**|em|
|**n**|n|**n̈**|en|
|**p**|p|**p̈**|pi|
|**q**|ku|**q̈**|kju|
|**r**|r|**r̈**|ɑr|
|**s**|s|**s̈**|es|
|**t**|t|**ẗ**|ti|
|**v**|v|**v̈**|vi|
|**x**|ks|**ẍ**|eks|
|**y**|j|**ÿ**|waɪ|
|**z**|z|**z̈**|zi|

The wiki for the [umlaut/diaeresis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diaeresis_(diacritic)#Latin_alphabet) doesn't have "d" "f" or "g" so I can't include them as of yet. I'm new to phonetics in general so I did my best above, but I may have made mistakes. The last column is problematic as I had to approximate based on English sound examples I could find. I know from the wiki for [IPA](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Phonetic_Alphabet) that there is a symbol for "name of the letter 'p'" or "**p̈"** like in the example

**"IPA" in IPA (\[aɪ pʰiː eɪ\])**

so I know other symbols are out there that may explain the fourth column better but I'm not advanced enough to recognize them. If there are better ways to show those sounds, please let me know.

**Worldbuilding** (if I may go on a tangent...)

Dü’osr̈aï is also artificial in the world it's set in as it's spoken on another planet, a colonized human planet, and created for the purpose of bringing the colonizers together to form a new culture. Assuming the trip is longer than a lifetime, our speakers find themselves plugged in and 'taught' the language while in cryogenic sleep, so everyone wakes up speaking it. One does not forget their original language, and a large percentage of the colonial population was able to speak English originally as a first or other language, which is 'why' it's heavily English inspired, canonically. I'm sure this isn't a new concept, but I have a 'real' population in a computer game I play and I enjoy writing about their lives and culture.

**Morphology** (terminations)

I said in the title that this language is meant to teach me more about my own language and flex my ability to learn others just a little. I also just wanted something I could learn quickly. Therefore I decided that most parts of speech would have a termination because I want to be able to easily identify them, with some exceptions to make it a tad less formulaic. So far I only have set endings for nouns/pronouns, adjectives, adverbs, and eight tenses of verbs, with a special ending for titles no matter what part of speech they were derived from.

|Noun/Pronoun|Adjective|Adverb|
|:-|:-|:-|
|\-**ï**|\-**öx**|\-**ïox**|

Titles (or the formal) end in - **ë** with the letter "**y**" used before when converting a noun. ( = **ïyë** ) The original ending stays in place, making these the only words with two endings after another. They aren't that important other than culturally but the same rule applies when making plurals (-**ïys̈)**

Plural nouns are conjugated to let us know whether the number of items is known, unknown, or unknowable to the speaker. (nötö'- is not always used, more formal, but can be used in place of "a"/"an")

|Singular|Known Plural|Unknown Plural|Unknowable Plural|
|:-|:-|:-|:-|
|\-**ï**|(**nötö')-ïys̈**|**ïgnö'-ïys̈**|**myë'-ïys̈**|

(Singular) a baby = **nötö'r̈evï** *or* **ä** **r̈evï**

(Known) three trees =  **trëöx r̈borïys̈**

(Unknown) some gold = **nonn̈ulöx ïgnö'r̈umïys̈**

(Unknowable) stars above = **myë'sölïys̈ s̈uprïox**

Verbs are meant to determine if the time frame is known, unknown, or unknowable as well. There are 8 tenses.

|Present|**-ix**|
|:-|:-|
|Present Continuous|\-**ïz**|
|Known Past|\-**ex**|
|Unknown Past|**-üx**|
|Unknowable Past|**-z̈üx**|
|Known Future|**-ill**|
|Unknown Future|**-üill**|
|Unknowable Future|**-z̈ill**|

I opened the door =  **Ï** **aperex z̈ ïanuï**

The door was opened (unknown) =  **Z̈** **ïanuï së'aperüx**

The stars were born (unknowable) = **Z̈ myë'sölïys̈ së'naẗz̈üx**

What exactly is unknowable may be varied, and that's okay, it's an estimation from the speaker. But when referring to a person engaged to be married you may say "You will get married!" ( in the known future if the date is set) while to console a single person you might say "You will find someone" (but the speaker could not know when).

Some things will be a matter of opinion in the moment. One of the translations of the day, for example:

"I saw a burned house (one that burned before I saw it)." = **Ï s̈pektöex ä** **dömï së'ign̈üx/së'ign̈z̈üx.**

The speaker was not there, so they cannot know when it burned, but they do know when they saw the building. The speaker may think there was no way for them to know when it burned since they weren't there, or that they simply don't know, but could have if they there when it burned. Either way is correct in this case.

**Grammar**

Practically English with some minor changes, but I want to shake it up more as I go.

Compound words are separated with an apostrophe to distinguish roots, and combinations of words based on how they're used in the sentence.

Prepositions and conjunctions don't have terminations and are sometimes used as a root in a compound and sometimes a separate word. I don't have the rules for exactly when down because I'm unsure about how to define it.

Auxiliary verbs also don't have terminations and are always combined with another verb. Any time two matching parts of speech are next to each other in the sentence they will come together. The first root is tacked on the front of the next word, such as:

**z̈ radu'güröx ïterï = the difficult, narrow road.**

**Vocabulary**

Just Latin thrown into a blender. I like Latin and want to learn roots, but I also want to put a spin on them, sometimes just taking a few letters from the most direct translation as I can find of an individual word and playing with it a bit.

Some simple words I found a filler for. I'm ambivalent about using z̈ for "the" and ä for "a" and so on but I'm at a loss on what I would like instead. These may stay the same but I'd like to try different ways of using articles, whatever they end up as.

**Translations**

I've been trying the translations of the day. Some samples (sorry my formatting is terrible):

​

⁖It seems that everything has been eaten.

⁖**Të’ideix öm̈nï së’osex.**

⁖Do-seems everything be-eaten.

​

⁖Julianne knew when he was born that her child would become chief.

⁖**Julïan nötex üan egï së’gënëex z̈ puer’gï öv'eqï ill̈de’fiöüill Rexï’gïyë.**

⁖Julianne knew when he be-born the (male) child of-her would-become King.

​

⁖Péter heard that who comes early, they admit him for free.

⁖**Pëter ar̈üx qömï venill an̈tëqïox, oläëys̈ dëmill oläë s̈ïn’ersïz.**

⁖Péter heard who will-come early, they (plural) will-allow them (singular) without-charging.

​

**What I need help with**

* The [wiki](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diaeresis_(diacritic)#Latin_alphabet) for the umlaut/diaeresis doesn't have "d" "f" or "g". If anyone could make or find a font to include a capital and lowercase version of these three letters that would help *immensely*.
* Grammar is lacking. Based on what I have and what feel you get from the samples, if any, how might I change things up? I don't like how many translations are 1:1 or very close. I need simple changes, but I'm open to suggestions and examples.
* Most things about glossing. I might understand how it needs to be done but not how to do it. What abbreviations do I use for concepts I made up? Or, is there a formal name for how I'm categorizing my verb tenses that I'm not aware of? If you'd like to gloss some of my translations that would be enlightening.

That's all I have, thank you so much if you got to the end. I would love to read your thoughts.

body:
There’s, “You can’t have dessert until you finish dinner.”

Then there’s, “You can’t leave the table and if you try to get food I will force you to eat it until you literally throw up.”

1 is annoying and can cause issues with food later in life.
2 is abusive. 

Absolutely NTA. Honestly, if the fridge was expensive enough, I’d take her to court (small claims, but I assume you live in Germany so whatever the equivalent is there). There is zero way I’d let her near your kid unsupervised. 

Imagine forcing a kid to eat something to intensely she vomits. And then trashing an (I’m assuming) at least €100 fridge. 

Do not let her with your upcoming son unsupervised either.

Jesus Christ. Times like these I wish there was a parent-in-law exchange center..

body:
I am getting one very soon! I am 32H, no kids, pretty young, but I can't wait, the pain and headaches are awful, I am way too petite for this size, lol. 

Everyone I have ever talked to regarding it has recommended it. I work in a lingerie store so I resize post reductions a lot and they rave about it. Honestly, not only will your pain go away but you'll have so much confidence. These women are just glowing after because they are so happy! Definitely have a chat with your GP to rule out other causes first and then discuss the actual surgery if you need :) I live in Canada and I did not have to pay out of pocket as it is considered "medically necessary" so you may have a chance not to depending on how your insurance is written. Good luck!

body: 7 years ago I was mid mental breakdown a few days after a rather traumatic event happened to me. I never took the bus anywhere other than from my high school to home at the time. I went to the park to drink til it was pretty late and when I went to go to the bus, I went the other way to a relatively empty train station. Other than me, there was only an old woman standing on the other side of the platform for a train heading the other way. I stood at the front end of the station waiting for the train to come through so I could throw myself in front of it. Just as the sign announcing the station changed to mark its incoming, I guess the old lady was watching me and realized what I was doing. She pulled me back as I was stepping forward. She couldn't speak english but she yelled at me anyway and started crying. She hugged me then got on the next train heading the other way, and I left and went home. I always think about her. I am thankful everyday for her, and I hope she's doing well.

title: [DK] Looking to trade with Asia or Australia
body:
For my third snack exchange I am looking for something that is not the US(not that I have anything against you guys :) ). 

I love doing exchanges, and am a huge fan of redditgifts.com, but I just wasn't feeling it this months, I'd rather get some snacks!                      

I am doing this exchange with my husband. 

We are thinking about sending ca. 1 kg, which will cost us 23 $ in shipping. Please research shipping prices from your destination before replying.                            
               
We live in Denmark, and among some of the things we do best is liquorice. But we have other things as well.           
We are not looking for anything specific, but rather just a selection of snacks that we do not have here, and that you think we need to try.                         
                
Please comment below if you think this might be something for you.

body:
I'm Danish, but maybe I can help anyway.

Round 1: knit2tog, do not transfer knit stitch to right needled, now knit into the first of the two knit together stitches, now transfer to right needle, knit one. repeat from *to*. This is a repeat of 3 stitches. 
Round 2 and 4: knit                                         
Round 3: Knit 1, knit2tog, without transferring the stitches to right needle, knit into first of the two knit together stitches. Repeat from * to *. Again a repeat of 3 stitches. 

I hope this makes sense. I knitted a small swatch, and it seems to work. Everytime you knit 2 together, you knit 2 into these, and thus always end up with 3 stitches.

body:
I'm a girl and 20 next month, I kinda had some time to accept it and love it the way I do today haha

It wasn't always that easy but I think that's obvious
The person I am the closest with in my life ( we're not officially in a relationship but everything looks like it ) does know though. I told him like three days after meeting him. It was at a dark time, I was suicidal and in my head I just wasn't going to stay for quite longer, so I just thought it didn't matter whether he'd leave or not. One year and a half later he's still here, so supportive, and helped me so much into finding meaning to stay, and can't thank him enough.
He's the only person who ever stayed once knowing my illness, so I just consider myself incredibly lucky, though I won't try my luck with my friends.

Well, I'm anonymous here so I don't mind explaining to you, don't worry you don't sound ignorant! You can't know until you try to know!

So actually I might not be the best exemple lmao, I'm both schizophrenic and have a multiple personality disorder, or at least saying it like that is the closest to what I have. I have a dozen person in my head, I can see and hear them, they live with me, they live everyday I live, they like, have a life of their own in my head. But sometimes I just won't be myself anymore. Those moments I don't necessarily remember, but it would be one of them in my body, if that's clear?

I do recognize when I'm starting to have an episode because of either of those things:
- I suddenly really struggle to breath and see blurry
- Everyone around me start talking the same and having the same face
- Perspectives are just not logically possible ( sometimes I just see a wall moving towards me faster and faster, the ground cracking before my feet, things like that )
- Every sound I hear feels like pain in my hears

Those are the more common for me, but as my doctor says, every schizophrenic person will have their personal symptoms, like every autistic person will live their disease differently. There's some level of schizophrenia for sure, but I would say it should be looked into for every person personally, if that makes sense in English ( I'm French, sorry if I'm making any mistakes )

body: Hello, I live in Latvia and have been to two psych wards. The one for teenagers and children is pretty shitty, but the one for adults (Tvaika iela) is actually very good and helped me a lot. Getting into a ward is actually much harder than you think, I have said some really fucked up things to my psychologist/therapist and they didn't put me in a ward as that's what psychiatrists do. So don't be afraid to open up to your therapist about things that bither you. Involuntary hospitalization js very rare.

body: We live in Latvia. Please don't trust USSR official reports for obvious reasons. I took a short look at your profile- the USSR isn't a funny topic, many people were killed and targeted by the KGB and my great grandfather was in a gulag and had to eat pine and fir needles for survival. For the sake of all people who died in the tyrannical regime, please stop defending it and making jokes. It is no laughing matter in this side of the world, please have respect.

body:
I agree, but much less aggressively. My commute to work includes a street with many, many, *many* stop lights. Yet people would rather walk inbetween cars whether they're stopped or not like life is a game of Frogger. I dont get angry, or judge them as being entitled, but I do feel very confused & concerned with a hint of annoyance. Like the crosswalk is literally 5 feet away! The light is going to be red in a few moments! Why is everyone walking in front of cars like this? Both of our days will be ruined! I have no clue how to explain that sort of situation to my insurance, I'd be crying on the phone incoherently with the paramedics and my auto insurance rep on the line because "what to do when you hit someone who randomly wandered in front of your car" is not a lesson taught in school. The pedestrian would be in agonizing pain, I would be so panicked I forget how to speak english, it would be a disastrous scene and I dont see how that's worth it. Just properly cross the street. 

 The way people cross the street just makes me scared for their safety. Except the ones who walk up to my car to scream at my driver side window when I'm stuck at a red light, then I'm scared for my own safety.

title: Left Lush after a year, here are my thoughts 🛁
body:
Pros:

- Really great people on my team. Everyone is so kind, friendly, and supportive. It felt like we were a little family and it was the healthiest work environment I’d been in. No gossiping, we’d give each other notes of encouragement, and constantly try to help each other out. 

- Okayish pay. Got to $18/hr by the time I left. Where I’m at, it just wasn’t cutting it unfortunately. 

- Discount is great, I loved when people ruined products so I could take them home, and constantly getting free goodies. I have probably 40ish bath bombs in my bathroom right now! 


Cons:

- Radio system is rarely RARELY updated, constantly replays the same music ESPECIALLY DURING HOLIDAY, and oftentimes stations are either broken (loops random jingles and beats) or outdated (Bridgerton station had like 10 songs and.. why do we need to play Bridgerton now…) 

- Snotty, expectant, rude, classist, and/or cruel customers. Lush is high end, it attracts high end clientele. People would demand me to do things, “Tell me about this,” “Give me one of these,” “I want you to do this.” Other times, I’d get backhanded comments like “oh, you use the toothpaste? Have you gotten some cavities?” or once I’d complimented an outfit, they responded “thank you! It comes in ALL sizes, too!” I’ve dealt with bratty and overwhelming kids with absent or permissive parents. Spoiled teenagers who ignored me. Groups of young adults who gave me side eyes and laughed when I tried to talk to them. I’ve been demanded to open NEW products to make samples for someone, someone walked into our back room and asked us where our restroom was (ours was not public), stay well past close to ask about EVERY AND ANY product, and so much more.

- Poor hygiene from customers. People will open NEW AND SELLABLE products, use them, and put them back on the self. It happens OFTEN. People will press items into their nose to smell, touching the product to their nose, mouth, or oftentimes their whole bottom half of their face. People touch EVERYTHING. People let their babies put things in their mouths then put it back. Will have their children with very visible pink eye touch bath bombs, rub their eyes, and repeat until one parent finally notices the oozing, puffy eye. We can’t write all of it off, especially when we only catch it after it’s already been happening. 

-Little to no benefits. Very basic and most times, your staff discount won’t cover everything you want. Merch, knot wraps, etc you get made. Collabs are 25%. 

- A HUGE push to sell without a good incentive to do so. If we do make our goal, we make maybe a $100-300 in bonus, which sounds awesome, but after stressing over sales, getting in trouble for not doing enough demos, having your team speed themselves thin.. it’s barely a prize after all it costs. 

- Was once told by a higher up visiting my shop that I needed to give a customer a demo, but I explained that since he was wearing headphones, I wasn’t going to disturb him. She then told me that when a customer wears headphones, it’s “just the same as when a customer doesn’t speak English. You do it on them anyway.” WHAT. So.. not knowing a certain language deprives you of your ability to consent? Cool. Awesome.

title: person from italy who needs new online friends :))
body:
hii! i'm Misanet, in August I'll be 14, I'm from Italy and I'm looking for new friends online, where I can talk. I am genderfluid and panromantic, and my MBTI personality is INTJ. 
i have schizophrenia so be patient with me please.
I like to draw, i have been drawing for two years, I can draw anime but also gacha but I use those as a reference.
i'm also into music and gaming, i like Minecraft, fnf (Friday Night Funkin') and horror games.
i like hyperpop, and glitchcore/weirdcore songs!
I am obsessed with an anime called "Junji Itou: Collection", and with one of the protagonists called Souichi Tsujii, i also saw danganronpa and hanako-kun, in fact i even like Byakuya Togami, Toko Fukawa, Miu Iruma,  Tsukasa and Hanako.
i'm very shy, and i don't have many social skills.
i hope i can make new friends here!

title: I'm scared of the future
body:
I live in Germany and I'm scared that a world war 3 will emerge because of the current conflicts in europe. I believe humanity will not survive world war 3. But that's beside the point, I just don't feel well mentally at all. I push through and try my best every day and I have made so many improvements, even with having paranoid schizophrenia it is currently possible for me to live a normal life. But then reality hits again like the current pandemic and as I said, war. I just pray the situation will get better and people all over the world realize at some point that weapons do not solve conflicts, they make them worse. Today someone asked me if I would wear a gun to defend myself. I honestly can't answer that question. Knowing myself, I would probably die because I space out when a situation gets too much for me to handle. Even just the thought of it is so horrifying I don't want to think about it more..

I am often alone and it makes me sad. Talking with other people where I am currently staying at makes my day, even if just for a little. Sometimes I wish I could help others more but I don't know how and I mess up a lot. I guess I need more help myself. Sometimes I wish there would be someone magically appearing out of somewhere and saving me from my misery, but I guess that's not gonna happen. Anyway, I hope everyone else has a nice weekend. And I pray that as many people as possible can be saved from war.

body:
Good evening friend, thanks for sharing your thoughts. I agree with you. I’m American, but I’ve also lived in Brazil off and on throughout the years for work/friends. I’ve noticed that in Brazil, the corruption is blatant and impossible not to see everywhere you go. Brazilians know this and they acknowledge it. They make jokes all the time about it, regardless of who is in office. In America it’s a bit different. I feel like the large majority understand that the government is corrupt, but we don’t acknowledge it as often because it’s much more secretive here than in Brazil. And, depending on which party is in office, many people will defend their political affiliation to the point of denying corruption. 

About LSA, first of all welcome to the Faith! It’s great to have you, my friend. I attended one LSA election just so I could see how it’s done (I didn’t vote and no one pressured me to) LSA elections are annual. We congregate at a members house and are given a list of all local members. You write down the names of who you vote for each position and put it in the ballot box. When everyone is done, two members will take the box to another room and count the votes. It’s a democratic process, so whoever has the most votes for a particular position will get it for the next year.

title: I’ll need therapy my whole life and it scares me
body:
Hello!
I’m sorry if I misspell some words, English is not my first language (I’m French :))
I just wanted to share some things about my life with people that may understand me 

I’ve been diagnosed with schizophrenia like 2 months ago, I’m 17. I think my illness is pretty light, because I don’t have that much hallucinations, even tho the negative symptoms are so strong that everybody thought I had depression, but that’s not the point. 

My therapist said that I’ll need therapy all my life and it was quite a shock. I always thought I had depression and it will go away with the years, but turns out I have a mental illness that stays forever. I’m so afraid, I don’t want to struggle my whole life. Life is so hard at this moment, it’s been worse and worse since I’m 13 (I also have anxiety disorder and I’m gifted (i’m not sure if it’s the right word, I mean I have a high iq)). I don’t see myself struggling that way my whole life, I don’t want to. I’m already so sad that I can’t fully enjoy my teenager years.

In the other hand, I feel like a fraud. I’m not even a heavy case, I shouldn’t complain. To tell you the truth, I don’t even believe myself that I’m schizophrenic, even tho all the doctors said it’s true.

I know I’m supposed to get better with time but for now it just keeps getting worse and worse. I’m really afraid of my future. I can clearly see my adult self losing her job and friends and not correctly eating / showering.

I’m sorry for the bad mood I’m bringing. Please take care of yourself.

body:
Cannons on MBT's aren't very well optimized for HE use. HE can be fired effectively on the field with recoilles rifles.   
   
Not arguing. Just explaining reasons why I said HE is less important now. Over generalizing statements like that are what causes problems like this.   
  
As I am from Finland I see view from Finlands perspective. Every finnish male gets conscripted so we know how our defense forces work. On the field we would just use recoilles rifles to deliver HE. Our small number of Leopard 2A6's are mainly for mobile anti tank purposes.

body:
Generation Zero, it's 5 bucks, just be sure to put the settings to enlish, otherwise I think they speak swedish.

Factorio or Satisfactory, Factorio is 2d and Satisfactory is 3d, their both factory games that slowly get more complicated as time goes on.

7 Days To Die, it's a fun zombie survival game that you can change a lot of settings on, also it is updated pretty often, every time I've come back to it, I've had a lot of fun.

Team Fortress 2, it's a free first person shooter with 9 classes, each with a lot of depth to them.

Borderlands 2, it's always pretty cheap I would say most the dlc is really good. It's just a looter shooter, and can be pretty funny at times.

Any soulborne from Fromsoftware, whether it be Dark Souls or Sekiro, provided you want a challenge.

Metal Gear Solid 5, really fun game to screw around in.

Risk of Rain 2, a rogue-like that has multiple classes to start out with and many upgrades and different game modes to play.

title: The whole world hates me
body:
I'm russian and i hate it. My country is a bloody dictatorship filled with propaganda and assholes. I dream of leaving here forever and never coming back, but i feel like i can't do that. Even if i could do it - i'm hated all over the world, everyone wants me dead. I feel that it's not the Ukrainians who should be under fire, but me. I dream that a rocket would fly into my house.  
You are considered not a human being, but a cog in the system. If you die, everyone is happy.  
I feel a huge sense of guilt and i want to die. The whole normal world will never accept me.   
I'm in a prison cell.

I found these links

[https://ilac101.com/ilac/trevicta-525-mg-im-enjeksiyon-13404/](https://ilac101.com/ilac/trevicta-525-mg-im-enjeksiyon-13404/)

[https://ilac101.com/ilac/xeplion-150-mg-1-5-ml-im-14406/](https://ilac101.com/ilac/xeplion-150-mg-1-5-ml-im-14406/)

Not sure if you're from Turkey/speak Turkish but "şatış fıyatı" means "price of sale" if you scroll down a bit. Only confusing bit to me is that the symbol after the price doesn't say TL (Turkish Lira).

Under the sale price it says "Yardım" ("Help") off to the left and then there's a yellow button saying "Mesaj Gönder" ("Send Message") - I'd wager if you sent them a message in English, you'd have a fair shot of getting one back in English, or you could use Google Translate.

Edit: Xeplion is what they call Invega in Turkey.

Edit2: To make things simpler for you, if the prices ARE in TL, you're looking at 192.37 USD for the Invega and 568.26 USD for the Trevicta.

title: A long and boring rant of a stupid teen
body:
I’ve talked with my psychiatrist and parents about my search for other people with schizophrenia of my age, I asked them for psychosis support groups and my psychiatrist told me, not exactly like this:

“You should look to be surrounded by healthier people, it’s like addicts, if you spend too much time with them you’ll probably become an addict too, so, if you spend too much time with other people with schizophrenia you’ll become unstable, as most of them are unstable”

I feel so happy while talking with other people with my illness, why can’t I do that? Why should I restrain myself from what I want? I want to help them if they are unstable, I just want to be happy, unstable people with this illness are not like addicts.

They would comprehend me if I start dissociating, they would know how to help me with other symptoms like hallucinations, they would relate to me so much.

People make fun of me, every time I fall in love I fail, and they find that funny, my mom makes fun of me because I fell in love with a girl that was so damn obvious I wouldn’t be able to be with, if they knew how empty I feel..., I don’t think it’s funny. I got excited because I thought this time I would make it, “I finally found someone my age with the illness” I was so happy, telling all my friends.

They were supportive, they told me I deserved to finally be with someone, she appeared to also like me, and I ruined it, I don’t know how, what did I do, maybe I just wasn’t her type, I know that’s just how love works.

Now I cry every night thinking this isn’t fair, thinking that’ll never find someone who loves me back. 

Maybe I’m being ridiculous; “You kidding? You live in Mexico and she lives in USA idiot” Told me my friend after I realized I would never make it. And indeed, now that I think about it I should have never tried, I shouldn’t have told her how I felt about her, I should have stayed as a friend.

“You’re entertaining cause you’re crazy haha” I was told once, I fucking hate my life.

“You should focus on publishing your book” my friends told me, at the same time telling me: “I won’t read your book unless you gift it to me”

Has someone even read to this point? I’m boring as fuck, crying because of shit everyone here has suffered from, and I just can’t bear it.

I’m still trying, I’m not gonna kill myself, not for a while at least.

“You shouldn’t be in a relationship if you’re so unstable, no one deserves having to bear your shit” It’s what I tell myself, I don’t deserve being with someone.

“You must be fucking kidding, you’re only 16 and you want to find the love of your life” A friend told me.

No one in my family apologized for hitting me so many times after I got diagnosed, maybe I’m asking for too much, they said: “that’s why he was so weird”.

I’m sorry for making you read all of this, I’m starting to dissociate right now, I’m gonna take my meds.

title: Just got Starlink, steam keeps "bricking" my internet connection on my PC. (Using a USB apadter)
body:
When ever I download games on steam, my entire PC has to be reset to connect back to my Starlink node. It downloads for maybe 2 minutes, then my entire PC's connection cutout, only my PC disconnects)

I can play games, but just downloading, it seems large files, "bricks" my PC's connection. (I use a USB "Linksys brand" wifi adapter that's about 2 years old. Maybe the adapter can't handle it?)

This never used to happen on my other internet connections. (Although they were alot slower.)

I'm from Australia so our normal internet is quite slow. Like 25Mb/s with regular cutouts while Starlink showed consistent 100+Mb/s.

body:
NAT

  
I'm from Australia, and have been in therapy with various professionals for about 1.25 years each, when ever I asked them what is wrong with me/what is my diagnosis, they always asked "Why do you want to know?" and then I told them I'd like to know so I can take appropriate steps to get better, and then still they never told me.

  
(I was with mostly clinical psychologists as well, so they can diagnose, even the psychiatrists I saw didn't tell me. I found my diagnosis through a letter that wasn't in my name, but it was a referral/talked about me so that I could get some social services.)

body:
I don't know how payment works in other countries, I am from Australia.

  
They "give you options", that lead to the same thing, except if you don't choose willingly the "option" is usually traumatic (involuntary hospitalisation). 

  
You're best bet is to just do as they say, you're in a bind.

body:
NAT, but I have a schizophrenia spectrum disorder.

I have searched for about 4 - 5 years for a "specialist" and no one advertises it at all. I'm from Australia though. The knowledge of schizophrenia spectrum disorders is woefully small, they assume medication works all the time or something stupid like that. Also, there are like 15 other things that go into a regular schizophrenia, other than "voices". I couldn't imagine how many things extra that go into schizoaffective.

So I settled with a psychodynamic therapist that understands (at least seems to understand) psychotic personality organisation/s.

title: Is forcing a child into extremely cold showers considered abusive?
body:
When I was 11 I went into foster care and my first foster mom wasn't that nice to me. But sometimes I think it was my fault. I didn't learn how to properly shower myself until I was 15. I'm Samoan with very ethnic hair and I didn't know how to take care of it at 10, neither did my foster. In the meantime they would get extremely annoyed at me and it escalated into being yelled at every morning. Literally every morning like she just woke up dreading having to deal with me. She'd wake me via throwing water at my face or ripping my mattress off the bed and I was told this is normal punishment for kids who acted like me.

Every morning she would turn the shower water to extremely cold temperatures and tell me to get in and I would and this would be the only way I could get help with washing my hair.

When it came time to rinse my hair she would turn the water to scolding hot. I have memories of her turning off the cold water off entirely and turning the hot water knob on. She said the heat was good for my hair. 

I remember thinking, "This really hurts. But she knows better than I do."

Does anyone have opinions on this? Again, people have told me that this is all normal. Cold showers are ways to punish without leaving bruises.

body:
>That can absolutely be true at the same time, I'm targeting the specific example of religious clothing, public schools, and coercion (particularly of girls) by religious groups.

Yeah laïcité laws is great, but you have to consider that some people are flocking to a stringent foreign identity because there is no path for them to become/feel French.

>Yet, I wouldn't hold up France as a phenomenal example of immigrant integration and assimilation at all.

There are plenty of immigration success stories but a lot of failures too.

> What would you like to see changed in France to make integration better?

Different immigrants have different needs.  Personaly I'm not French (yet) but my father is so there isn't much effort to do in order to feel French, but I can see how hard it is for other immigrants

title: [PC][NA-East] Team SHUTDOWN.exe looking for 1 Tank/DPS Flex
body:

Something I want to emphasize — your SR does not matter! Additionaly, we already have a Rein and D.VA main, so if those are your mains, this opportunity may not be for you.
Requirements: -Microphone -Discord -Speak English -PC Overwatch -NA Region (preferably East Coast) -NOT SALTY
We will probably play several hours a week, on Saturday or Sunday — whatever works best.

body:
I am senseimuffin (#1241), and I just started Team SHUTDOWN.exe. I am looking for 5 players who are willing to practice (QP), and scrim — possibly enter tournaments in the future. Something I want to emphasize — your SR does not matter!

Requirements:
-Microphone
-Discord
-Speak English
-PC Overwatch
-NA Region (preferably East Coast)
-NOT SALTY

I will be looking for 1 more support (not Lucio, that's what I play) 2 tanks, 1 DPS and 1 Flex (can play tank and DPS). We will probably play several hours a week, on Saturday or Sunday — whatever works best.

Looking forward to practicing and improving as a team!
-senseimuffin

body:
It's unclear to me whether the groups you're talking about are Baha'i or just people in your wider community. 

There are a great many things to consider as to why people may not choose to speak English, or stay within ethnic communities. It likely has nothing to do with race unity or thinking other races or languages or whatever are wrong or lesser-than, and more to do with other things like possibly not feeling confident speaking English, fearfulness of the majority groups, racism they may experience, economic and age factors...it probably would be a different answer for different people. For many groups of people English is a language that has been forced, it's a language of colonisation, in that sense it can be painful to speak. 

Have you tried learning or taking an interest some of the languages they speak or their culture?

It might take forming long term relationships and building trust with people before they feel comfortable speaking in English to you. Perhaps they might not be interested in talking about race relations or unity.

body:
These have already been suggested ITT but...I live in New Zealand, ground zero for all things LOTR/Hobbit. 

Getting LOTR themed wedding rings is a great idea...and not unusual at all. Where I work, which sells fine jewlery, we have 'official' LOTR jewelry including gold 'one' rings. They are 9kt gold and many people choose these for wedding bands. They look like regular bands until you get close to them, they have etched elvish on them. Check out [the Weta Cave](https://www.wetanz.com/), the giftshop attached to Weta Workshops, perhaps there are some small accessories?

Alternatively, is it possible to take a honeymoon or trip to NZ? You could visit Hobbiton and visit some of the places that were used while filming LOTR. That's an expensive idea, but perhaps something he might be on board with that you both could do together in celebration of your marriage.

title: Is early game of Yi so bad as they say?
body:
Hi guys I'm chilean sorry my english

I play in LAS, currently in bronze, yeah, I'm bad I know (less than 1 year playing).

My mains are Master Yi and Xin Zhao and I have to disagree with people that say that **MASTER YI HAS A BAD EARLY GAME.**

Why? It is true that Yi doesn't have powerful ganks, but in 1 v 1 duels, I won almost all of them, I beat Xin Zhao, even Lee Sin, how? Because of the powerful W of Master Yi, I try to use it well and I mitigate all the damage of any champ and I beat them.

Do you agree? What's your opinion on Master Yi's early game?

I'm chilean and had never heard the cheese term. So I googled "cheese game meaning" and I found this:
  

  
(in a game, especially a video game) to win (a battle round) by using a strategy that requires minimal skill and knowledge or that exploits a glitch or flaw in game design
  

  
https://www.dictionary.com/browse/cheesing
  

  
So, I don't know which is the contradiction by associating cheese with minimal skill.

body:
Why in this webpage people always answer like this. He is asking and you take him like an idiot. I've done some questions here and two of them answered like this, with question marks.

I'm not from United States and I don't know if it comes from the culture of U.S. people or from english internet culture. This sucks and doesn't make a community to be healthy especially for new people.

I've played Aatrox jg because I'm jungler and I like Aatrox. One time I searched about it and people say he isn't good because he doesn't farm well and doesn't have gank resources. I think they are mostly right. From my experience playing him jungle a lot of times it is right that you don't farm well in first minutes, he clears slow at the beginning. So you should seek gank opportunities (he is an early champion aswell). Here comes the second: I don't agree much that you don't have gank resources. You will always burn flashes if you hit your W, so there you have a good tool to gank.

You can try Aatrox jg if you like him, but you will have mainly the disadvantage of being a slow clearer without having a hypergank kit in return. This doesn't mean you can't gank anyway.

Im also on disability but feel like if i can get some sleep properly every night instead of sometimes i might be able to work. i would give my number but im a bit paranoid about doing that and my phones broken.I also live in Aus so no point i guess.

I like olanzopine its the only med that has worked for me but feel i gain weight on it since reaching 40 years old three years ago.

I hope you find some good people on here, i luckily have a gardener who i talk to every day and introduced me to a lot of people...but without him or my family i would be lost.Maybe you should seek getting a carer who helps you etc if possible, i know it is in Aus.

title: Looking for a "listening exchange"
body:
Hi guys

This is Alberto, from Spain, and I really like telling my problems to a psychologist (curiously, I got that degree)because **Ï find it really desstressing but I find really expensive to pay 50 euros** (about 60 USD) to talk one our. I know its a great effort finishing that career, but I simply cannot afford it. And I find really diffficult to find friends that I can explain some issues and felt really listened, even to my girlfriend.

But I think that I am also a good listener, and If anyone wants, I would try the next thing:

**15/15 -> 15 minutes one listen and 15 minutes the other one.** Maybe like a therapist/patient and then patient/therapist relationship; but focusing in listening rather than giving advice (but anyone can do that if he wants). If we like it, we can repeat of course. I would like to do this as many times as I can (with different people)

The only difficult is that I am not a native English speaker, I am from Spain. But if anyone doesnt mind that I'll speak a bit slower, it would be great.

On what dosage of Abilify are you? It helps with motivation?

body:
I am diagnosed with schizophrenia and I got a job, girlfriend, friends and family. 10 years ago I had 2 psychotics breaks and I have been depressed about 3 years (nowadays I am on and off... maybe in the most stressful moments....)

​

I don't come here to brag, is just I want to encourage people to keep improving their mental health. I have to say that I am really lucky and, despite effort, I think not everybody would be able to almost recover. This is also a matter of luck. 

However, I think everybody should give a try things like psychology, sport, nutrition and talking about meds to their pdoc.

Summary: started on 10 mg risperdal and antidepressants, nowadays 3.6 abilify (less than 2mg risperdal) and 50mg lamotrigine. I have improved my relation with meds being very regular and not making big changes, I always negotiate with my pdoc. But be careful: [https://www.survivingantidepressants.org/](https://www.survivingantidepressants.org/)

\- Always interested in psychology. I go to a humanist psychologist and I do Cognitive Behavioural Teraphy through an app: Woebot.

I have no economic interest at all. But Woebot let me to manage stress much better and thanks to it i have been able to work. For me has helped more than any other thing, even psychologist in person. (But a person help you in other ways, I also recommend it)

\- Take care about nutrition: there are a lot of information, maybe too much. But I think everybody agree that trying to avoid sugar is a good point to start, for example.

[https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/when-your-adult-child-breaks-your-heart/201506/eating-optimal-mental-health](https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/when-your-adult-child-breaks-your-heart/201506/eating-optimal-mental-health)

\- Sport: many people tells wonders about physical activity. However, I am "too lazy" to heavy or moderate sport (I usually walk). I have to explore this side

​

PS: sorry for my English, I am from Spain.

body:
Thank you! I think programming in Unity is a good choice. I had to do some programming for VR in another job and I find really interesting when you code something and they push "play" to see the results. That was important, an "early feedback", having quick feedback in your tasks (I don't know how to say it, I am spanish hehe)

Now I have a tip, because I am realizing that I can't see a whole youtube video without getting extremely bored. But I can do Java exercises. Just google java for beginers and that is really interesting, doing, doing and doing.

I have read some theory, but I have to be careful with this, because it gets extremely tired if the "practical part" doesn't come along with the theory. And it is not useful.

So, this is my tip right now (I am starting), wether you see theory or not... always practice. Even small exercises.

body:
Maybe you can try to think about this like a "music rehearsal" of going to class in your life.

I mean: you are young and maybe you can think about this like a first try, your life is long and there will be much other opportunities of going to class (and to make your parents proud of you, if that is worrying you in some way). Maybe you can see it as a test, try not to see this as a "longlife" condition, maybe a temporal one that you can take advantage of it as a way to find what you really want in life.

Also another trick if you want to do, is to talk maybe with a teacher that you feel can be supportive. I did that and I feel much more comfortable in class.

But, what is the matter with the university? why you don't like it?

Sorry for my English, I am from Spain.

body:
Yes, I'm Polish. The books are very good and probably much better than the movie. But I think that they are a lot of things that were hard to translate. The book is very Polish and Slavic, they take part of that into account when translating the movie into Polish. Like the main character says "fuck" at different times and they didn't translate that into the common Polish curse word "kurwa", only the one that was in the book that is not very common in spoken language.

Right now there will be a premier of 3rd series (in two parts), and the main actor (Henry Cavil) left, probably because he didn't like how they mess with the original book.

You can watch the movie (it's on Netflix) and if you like it you can read the books.

title: What is "having schizophrenia" called in your language?
body:
As title said. I'm just curious because I'm danish and in Denmark we learn to not say "I'm schizophenic' and instead say "I have/suffer from schizophrenia" when you get your diagnosis. It's like you dont say "I'm cancer" but "I have cancer" because it's an illness. 

 So I was wwondering if this is something uniqe or other countries do it as well?

body:
Well, okay, but it's still a horror movie. You don't watch Midsommar to see a fairytale.

I get what he means, but it's still a horror movie, with horror elements.

I'm danish, so I'm pretty well-known about fairytales, and I don't see it. There's none of the typical tropes or anything. I get that it doesn't have to have like, three talking animals that warns you, to be a take on fairytales, but it does have to have some connection to it.  
I only watched it once though, without knowing that at all, so I could miss something though.

body:
Why do you just assume they would agree because of money and a US citizenship?

That's an incredibly selfish train of thought.

Greenland is a country with a rich and deep history and culture and love for their country.

Not everything is about the US, and a lot of us actually feel very lucky and fortunate to be born where we are, I'm Danish myself and I feel I hit the jackpot by being born Danish.

Love for your country isn't an American idea.

No matter how much money and free US citizenship or not, I would never leave Denmark, I love this place. Don't you think the people of Greenland are capable of feeling the same about Greenland?

body:
Denmark. Probably something with Greenland. Greenland is part of the kingdom of Denmark, and we've really fucked them over in some ways.. like, removing their children from their homes and making them grow up and become social experiments.
I honestly don't Know a lot about it, but denmark/Greenland have a very, idk, unhealthy relationship. 
Like, they have to learn danish in school, but Ive also heard that going to live in Denmark, for them is seen as a defeat. It's rock bottom. 
Ive seen and known a lot of Greenlanders in my life here in Denmark, and very of few of them werent alcoholics or homeless or something. 

We even have a word, for being so drunk, its trashy and you have no idea whats going on. It's "grønlænder-stiv", which translates to "Greenlander-wasted".

body:
I’m from Denmark. All students (or at least 95%) receive monthly payments from the government (it’s called SU) as long as they’re active in their studies. People with schizophrenia, or other diagnoses of the same potency (difficult BPD, disorders, disabilities, etc.), are eligible to receive double payments. Meaning, that I’m able to receive double my monthly support as long as I don’t work and am active in my studies. 

Besides that I also receive free treatment for two years, with medication included.

I’m from Denmark, so a JS palette is around 75+ dollars and a Morphe would be around 52+ dollars. You can’t buy them psychically either so it’s strictly from online shops. We have taxes on top of the order (that already has taxes in it) and a toll, I guess you would call it that, that rises depending on how much it weighs and how far it’s travelled.

EDIT: To make it easier — it’s not uncommon for me to have to pay (at least) 100 dollars for one palette.

title: Does anybody else have the situation where others think you look non-white even if you personally think you look white?
body:
I keep getting asked what country I'm from. And when I respond saying I'm American they ask, "Where are you \*really\* from?" I also get asked if I am indigenous (Native American to be precise) several times over the course of my life. I eventually asked somebody I see often about this and they said I looked more indigenous than white. I have a few more examples but I believe you guys have the gist of it.

I have always considered myself being able to pass well as white. Although only due to the fact I have light skin.

title: I found my ducks in a strange spot.
body: There is a stairway by my house on the outside. This morning I went outside and and my grandma said "Quack Quacks esta aya" (something like that. She doesn't speak English. And she calls ducks Quack Quacks so I understand her, though I know how to say duck in Spanish ). I looked and I saw the ducks standing at the bottom of the stairs. My brother was there and he took the first duck up the stairs to the yard. When he went to get the other duck, the duck was climbing up the stairs. We were pretty surprised to see that considering that duck is really heavy (Pekin duck). She met up with the other duck once she got to the top of the stairs. We still don't know how the ducks got down there.

title: [TOMT][1990s-2000s][Movie]A choose your own adveture type movie
body:
So I have this movie(?) from my childhood, probebly from the late 90s early 2000s judging from the animation. It's a choose-your-own-adventure type of movie where it pauses and let's you choose betwene diffrent routes.

Ok so the things I remember are there is this guy, a young boy who looks like Link(from legend of zelda) but in purple clothes or maybe he was just dressed in purple and had purple or blue hair, he's on a quest to find either his sister or his love intrest from pirates that either were ghosts or worked with ghosts.

I remember a few part or scenes from the movie one is basicly the "guy" who gets the choise to either to ride on a flying ship through a wormhole or to avoid it and ride the long way, the wormhole is just a steriotypical hole through time and space in purple and black(maybe blue) only it is in the clear blue sky and you can see the "tunnel".

The outher part I remember was like a ecyclopedia of all of the creatchers in the movie and this purple clad fat, short, yellow guy that told the viewer about them, the most important one(from what i recal) are the "Squig" or something like that, they are basicly those green frog looking creatcher in the begining of the rick and morty intro but really tall and with a camoflage pattern that chaches colour depending on it's mood.

Can't for the life of me find anything from or about this movie not as much as a screenshot let alone the name. Any help is welcome.

I'm swedish by the way.

body:
I've really branched out, my current projects are in 100% cotton and another in a wool/alpaca mix. I enjoy the sensations in my hands of the alpaca mix. It's definitely more expensive but I like to match the best fiber for the job. I have baby camel, linen and llama yarn waiting to be used as well.

I'm from Denmark, so I don't think my sources would be very helpful to you. I don't know where you'd get natural fibers for a decent price in the US, but maybe that would make for a good r/crochet discussion!

body:
I am from Denmark where it is definitely a thing and he is from England where it is also definitely a thing. When I was looking for the customs regarding Leap Day proposals it seemed to be a thing only in European countries.  For instance the Wikipedia page says 

>In upper-class societies in Europe, if the man refuses marriage, he then must purchase 12 pairs of gloves for the woman, suggesting that the gloves are to hide the woman's embarrassment of not having an engagement ring.



Obviously in modern times, a woman can propose whenever but I like the tradition in this case.
